Windrop is a Cygwin Windows port of Eggdrop IRC Bot

windrop-1.10.0-compilecleaning.exe is a 7-Zip 24.09 self-extracting archive https://www.7-zip.org

$ sha256sum windrop-1.10.0-compilecleaning.exe
05062e2fe69dcc0db84c3e89dfa21674dc3b8b15f78a0e6cb52991370af06dc9  windrop-1.10.0-compilecleaning.exe

$ gpg --verify windrop-1.10.0-compilecleaning.exe.sig windrop-1.10.0-compilecleaning.exe
gpg: Signature made Wed 09 Apr 2025 12:35:26 PM CEST
gpg:                using RSA key 9117B74600C5801EE6616D86EEE2F7AD6B411573
gpg: Good signature from "Michael Ortmann (git sign) <ortmann@posteo.de>" [ultimate]

This Windrop includes:
- eggdrop 1.10.0-compilecleaning https://www.eggheads.org
- botnetop 1.5 module https://github.com/michaelortmann/botnetop.mod
- gseen 1.4.5 module https://github.com/michaelortmann/gseen.mod
- stats 1.15 module https://github.com/michaelortmann/stats.mod
- cygwin 3.6.0 https://cygwin.com
- openssl 3.4.1 https://openssl-library.org
- tcl 8.6.16 https://tcl.tk
- zlib 1.3.1 https://www.zlib.net
- 64 bit

Last official Windrop release was Windrop 1.8.3, so this alternative was
created until hopefully the official Windrop team resumes releasing new
versions.

Eggdrop: https://www.eggheads.org
Windrop: https://windrop.sourceforge.net

How to compile (steps to reproduce) Windrop 1.10.0:

Install Cygwin, select packages:
- autoconf2.7 2.72-1
- automake1.17 1.17-1
- binutils 2.44-1
- gcc-core 12.4.0-3
- git 2.45.1-1
- make 4.4.1-2
- mingw64-x86_64-gcc-core 12.4.0-1
- cygwins openssl can be used:
  libssl3 3.0.16-1 and openssl 3.0.16-1
  but i compiled openssl 3.4.1 instead
- cygwins tcl can be used:
  tcl 8.6.12-1 and tcl-devel 8.6.12-1
  but i compiled tcl 8.6.16 instead
- zlib-devel 1.3.1-1

Compile OpenSSL 3.4.1:
$ curl -LO https://github.com/openssl/openssl/releases/download/openssl-3.4.1/openssl-3.4.1.tar.gz
$ tar -zxf openssl-3.4.1.tar.gz
$ cd openssl-3.4.1
$ ./config --prefix=/opt/openssl-3.4.1
$ make
$ make install

Compile Tcl 8.6.16:
# use git instead of release tarball because 1 commit must be reverted
$ git clone https://github.com/tcltk/tcl.git
$ cd tcl
$ git checkout core-8-6-16
# the following git revert is because eggdrop needs libtcl8.6.dll.a
$ git revert b29ad5dcf260d9aa15a3a6ec5ff68a6cea255dd1
$ cd unix
$ ./configure --prefix=/opt/tcl-8.6.16
$ make
$ make install
# the following copy is also because eggdrop needs libtcl8.6.dll.a
$ cp libtcl8.6.dll.a /opt/tcl-8.6.16/lib

Compile Eggdrop 1.10.0-compilecleaning:
$ git clone https://github.com/eggheads/eggdrop.git
$ cd eggdrop
$ vi src/version.h
#   define EGG_PATCH "compilecleaning-windrop"
$ cd src/mod
$ git clone https://github.com/michaelortmann/botnetop.mod.git
$ git clone https://github.com/michaelortmann/gseen.mod.git 
$ git clone https://github.com/michaelortmann/stats.mod.git
$ cd ../..
$ EGG=/opt/windrop-1.10.0-compilecleaning
$ ./configure --prefix=$EGG --enable-strip --with-ssllib=/opt/openssl-3.4.1/lib --with-sslinc=/opt/openssl-3.4.1/include --with-tcllib=/opt/tcl-8.6.16/lib/libtcl8.6.dll.a --with-tclinc=/opt/tcl-8.6.16/include/tcl.h
$ make config
$ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/opt/openssl-3.4.1/lib:/opt/tcl-8.6.16/lib PATH=$PATH:/opt/openssl-3.4.1/bin:/opt/tcl-8.6.16/bin make eggdrop
$ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/opt/openssl-3.4.1/lib:/opt/tcl-8.6.16/lib PATH=$PATH:/opt/openssl-3.4.1/bin:/opt/tcl-8.6.16/bin make install
$ cp src/mod/botnetop.mod/botnetop.conf $EGG
$ cp src/mod/gseen.mod/gseen.conf $EGG
$ cp src/mod/gseen.mod/*.lang $EGG/language/
$ cp src/mod/stats.mod/stats.conf $EGG
$ cp src/mod/stats.mod/language/* $EGG/language/
$ cp -r src/mod/stats.mod/templates $EGG
$ cd $EGG
$ rm eggdrop.exe
$ mv eggdrop.exe-1.10.0 eggdrop.exe
$ rm -rf modules
$ mv modules-1.10.0 modules
$ cp /opt/openssl-3.4.1/bin/cygcrypto-3.dll .
$ cp /opt/openssl-3.4.1/bin/cygssl-3.dll .
$ cp /bin/cygwin1.dll .
$ cp /bin/cygz.dll .
$ cp /opt/tcl-8.6.16/bin/libtcl8.6.dll .
$ mkdir lib
$ cp -r /opt/tcl-8.6.16/lib/tcl8 lib
$ cp -r /opt/tcl-8.6.16/lib/tcl8.6 lib

Test under GNU/Linux Wine:
$ uname
Linux
$ wine --version
